SECOND REGULAR SESSION
HOUSE BILL NO. 3138
103RD GENERAL ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY REPRESENTATIVE SMITH (68).
6918H.01I JOSEPH ENGLER, Chief Clerk
AN ACT
To amend chapter 85, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to missing persons.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the state of Missouri, as follows:
Section A. Chapter 85, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto one new section, to be
2 known as section 85.705, to read as follows:
85.705. 1. Beginning January 1, 2027, a missing persons unit shall be established
2 within any police department located in a county with more than one million
3 inhabitants. The unit shall provide services deemed necessary to aid in the location of
4 missing persons including, but not limited to:
5 (1) Coordinating and investigating reports of missing persons;
6 (2) Collecting and disseminating information regarding missing persons in order
7 to assist in locating such persons, including entry of the missing person's information
8 into the Missouri Uniform Law Enforcement System (MULES) and the National Crime
9 Information Center (NCIC) system;
10 (3) Establishing a system for communication of information relating to persons
11 reported as missing; and
12 (4) Coordinating and communicating with the Missouri state highway patrol's
13 missing persons unit established under section 43.402.
14 2. Any police department located in a county with more than one million
15 inhabitants may hire additional officers and staff or may assign officers or staff
16 currently employed by the department to the missing persons unit. Compensation and
EXPLANATION — Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in the above bill is not enacted and is
intended to be omitted from the law. Matter in bold-face type in the above bill is proposed language.

